The paper discusses the evaluation of defenses against adversarial examples, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields of computer science. However, given the focus on security evaluations, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses machine learning techniques and computer vision, which suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes new methods for evaluating defenses, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SE (Software Engineering).
